py-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ecw1665702715443.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecw1665702715443.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecw1665702715443.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ecw1665702715443\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      System Menu (SysMenu)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the Windows system menu and buttons to minimize, maximize, and close the window are available for this window. Valid values: <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__section_w1145ab1b5b1_w1146ab1b5_w1147ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">True</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__2\">The title bar contains a button in the left\n                        corner, enabling the user to access the Windows system menu. Default if\n                           <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">Normal</code>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11000e1_d11001e1_d11002e1__entry__2\"> The system menu is disabled and cannot be\n                        displayed. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__section_thj_drl_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d299851e121\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__table_d11003e1_d11004e1_d11005e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Caption</span> property is <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>,\n                           the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">System Menu</span> property cannot be set.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__section_mfr_2rl_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d299851e170\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__p_d97571e1_d97572e1_d97573e1\">When the system menu is disabled, it is also not\n            possible to use keystrokes to minimize, maximize, or close the window. The title bar\n            contains no buttons to perform these actions. You can close the window using <span class=\"ph keypress\">Ctrl+F4</span>, but there is no Close button.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__section_fxv_hrl_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d299851e182\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__ul_l2l_3rl_4wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__li_d39578e1_d39579e1_d39580e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ecw1665702715443__li_d39581e1_d39582e1_d39583e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1705472567076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1705472567076.html\" title=\"An application shell is the first object that is executed when a Windows or character mode application is started. It determines how the application is initialized and the first form component that is displayed.\">Application Shells for Desktop Applications</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612735\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612735\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "System Menu (SysMenu) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 System Menu (SysMenu) Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the Windows system menu and buttons to minimize, maximize, and close the window are available for this window. Valid values: True or False . Value Description True The title bar contains a button in the left corner, enabling the user to access the Windows system menu. Default if Window Type is Normal . False The system menu is disabled and cannot be displayed. Usage Dynamic? No Dependencies: If the Caption property is False , the System Menu property cannot be set. Description When the system menu is disabled, it is also not possible to use keystrokes to minimize, maximize, or close the window. The title bar contains no buttons to perform these actions. You can close the window using Ctrl+F4 , but there is no Close button. Applies To Form Application Shells for Desktop Applications Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}